- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on sparsification of social networks and their structural properties. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper mentions the use of the open-source network analysis tool suite NetworKit. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper deals with network properties and their preservation. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possibility as the paper proposes a new sparsification method and compares it with existing ones. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a possibility as the paper deals with network analysis and sparsification.
